summary: The document is a declassified record associated with the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It discusses individuals, specifically MUNSELL and WISE, highlighting their backgrounds, questionable loyalty, and associations that raised security concerns. The document also mentions project RIALIVE and a withdrawn assignment to Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, due to these security issues.
key_findings: The document references the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It details individuals with questionable loyalty and associations, focusing on MUNSELL and WISE.
MUNSELL's employment was disapproved due to security concerns stemming from associations at Denver University.
Project RIALIVE is mentioned, along with a withdrawn assignment to Dhahran, Saudi Arabia, due to security concerns.
WISE's background includes attendance at Searcfele High School and allegations of Communist influences.
